%% state_07_user_status.mmd — User Status
%% Ref: user model (status: active/inactive/suspended)
%% Auth: OAuth only (Google/GitHub), no email/password
%% Soft delete via deleted_at column

stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> active : User registered\n(via OAuth: Google/GitHub)

    active --> inactive : Admin deactivates\nor user self-deactivates
    active --> suspended : Admin suspends\n(policy violation)
    active --> soft_deleted : Admin soft-deletes\n(SET deleted_at)

    inactive --> active : Admin reactivates
    inactive --> suspended : Admin suspends
    inactive --> soft_deleted : Admin soft-deletes

    suspended --> active : Admin lifts suspension
    suspended --> inactive : Admin deactivates
    suspended --> soft_deleted : Admin soft-deletes

    soft_deleted --> [*]

    note right of active
        System roles:
        • superadmin — full system access
        • system_admin — user management
        • registered_user — default role
        ──────────────────
        OAuth only — no email/password.
        Login creates user if not exists.
    end note

    note left of soft_deleted
        Soft delete: deleted_at ≠ NULL.
        User data preserved but inaccessible.
        Cannot be reversed (permanent).
    end note
